**Project: "Vegan Rob's Coin Cryptocurrency Platform"**

**About us:**

Congratulations on being invited to the challenge stage of the application process. We’re excited to find someone incredibly talented to work alongside us to bring many software projects to life. 

**Why This Challenge?**  
Vegan Rob’s Coin is a cryptocurrency developed by the Vegan Rob’s Snacks brand, which is a maker of chips and puffs sold nationwide. The Vegan Rob’s token cryptocurrency project is a brand pursuit of the Vegan Rob’s Snacks company aimed at tackling the world hunger issue.

With so many “experts” out there, it’s hard to know who to trust. We live for getting healthy vegan snacks to the public and look to improve the world by providing access, investing energy, and infusing crypto/blockchain technologies into a solution for the monumental food crisis across the globe.

We know this is only a small part of a solution, but we ask you to come along with us on our journey towards making the world even a little bit better.

https://veganrobstoken.com

**What’s In It for You?**

* A chance to work on a meaningful project that helps vegan snacks to the public and world accessible.  
* Showcase your ability to integrate web3 libraries to React front-end websites.

**Challenge Overview:**  
You’ll work on fixing some critical issues on the Web3 integration and smart contract API calls:

1. When users who don't have an installed wallet yet click the connect wallet button, it throws an error on the front-end side and it's breaking the entire flow of the project.  
   This is our TOP priority issue for now.  
2.  When you go to the vote page, you will be able to see that there is already one item voted there, but as you can see there, we cannot find its image.  
   Obviously, we uploaded an image together, but cannot find it.  
   I am not sure if this error comes from smart contract or web3 integration.  
   If it comes from smart contracts, the problem would be much more complex than expected..  
   => The source image turn out to be [vrdao's pinata cloud](https://vrdao.mypinata.cloud/ipfs/QmPyj3DrYwou8ruEJDYYRY17R4e7FEMaFuS1q7e74sP1tg). The actual gateway is not accessible, seem like the storage is deleted, quick solution is to modify the image link in election data.
3. When you go to the dashboard, you will be able to see the DAO information such as owner's address, members' address there.  
   You can see this information only when you connect the wallet, that works well. But the problem is when you disconnect the wallet. I want to hide DAO information when you disconnect wallet but it's still displaying even you disconnect wallet,   
   Our goal here is to hide them when you disconnect the wallet without full page refresh.

**Time:**

* This should take about 2-3 hours of focused development time.
